    {
      "id": "overview",
      "title": "Role Overview",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "content": {
            "text": "QA Engineer interviews assess your testing methodology, automation skills, and ability to be a quality advocate within development teams. Modern QA roles increasingly require coding and automation expertise."
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "content": {
            "text": "**What interviewers assess:**\n\n- Testing methodologies and strategies\n- Test automation skills\n- Bug identification and reproduction\n- Quality process improvement\n- Collaboration with developers"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "format",
      "title": "Common Interview Format",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "content": {
            "text": "**Typical QA interview loop:**\n\n1. **Recruiter screen** (30 min)\n2. **Technical phone screen** (60 min) - Testing scenarios or automation\n3. **Onsite/Virtual loop** (4-5 hours):\n   - Test case design exercise\n   - Automation/coding round\n   - Bug investigation scenario\n   - Behavioral round"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "tip",
          "content": {
            "text": "When given a feature to test, think beyond happy paths. Edge cases, error handling, security, and performance are where bugs hide."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
